model.implementations.components.manifests

Class ManifestImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.implementations.components.manifests.BasicManifest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Manifest
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AssetManifest, CompoundManifest, UnionManifest

    public abstract class ManifestImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements Manifest
    A manifest is an entity that describes assets, compounds and atoms by recording metadata about them. A manifest is not updatable. Manifests are publishable within the sea of stuff and allow discoverability of assets, compounds and atoms. Manifests are represented as a set of labels and values.
    Author:
    Simone I. Conte "sic2@st-andrews.ac.uk"
